attributes.Long form description: The student disassembles a table. He starts by slightly unscrewing all the hex socket heads from the table. After that, he unscrews the eight top hex socket heads that hold the table. Once the student releases the table, he continues to unscrew the bottom eight hex socket heads that hold the shelf together. The student divides the four legs, the table, and the shelf to complete the task.

attributes.Transcription: All right now we're going to disassemble this furniture.

attributes.Action sentence: The student unscrews the first leg of the table slightly.

attributes.Transcription: You should start by slightly unscrewing all the screws of the shelf.

attributes.Action sentence: The student slightly unscrews the second leg of the table.
The student slightly unscrews the third leg of the table.
The student slightly unscrews the fourth leg of the table.

attributes.Transcription: Now you can put the furniture on the side and fully remove the top shelf.

attributes.Action sentence: The student unscrews two legs of the table.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student drops the Allen wrench.

attributes.Action sentence: The student unscrews two legs of the shelf.
The student disassembles the last two legs of the shelf.

attributes.Transcription: Its over you can press the stop button
